<%- include('partials/head') %>
<section class="panel">
  <div class="panel-head">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Setup Docs</p>
      <h2>GS Agent and Automation Setup</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button" href="/setup">Setup Wizard</a>
      <a class="button" href="/downloads">Downloads</a>
      <a class="button" href="/compatibility">Compatibility</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="muted">Use this guide to prepare a workspace for paid automation. The website stores user-owned data and queues jobs. GS Agent and GS Browser Automator run the visible local work and report safe status back to the website.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-grid">
  <% docs.forEach(section => { %>
    <article class="panel">
      <div class="panel-head">
        <h2><%= section.title %></h2>
        <span class="status <%= section.status === 'Working' ? 'ready' : section.status === 'Scaffolded' ? 'needs_review' : 'working' %>"><%= section.status %></span>
      </div>
      <p class="muted"><%= section.body %></p>
    </article>
  <% }) %>
</section>

<section class="panel">
  <div class="panel-head">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Installation Flow</p>
      <h2>Recommended local setup order</h2>
    </div>
    <span class="tag"><%= download.available ? `Installer v${download.version}` : 'Installer coming soon' %></span>
  </div>
  <div class="setup-timeline">
    <article>
      <strong>Download GS Agent</strong>
      <p class="muted">Use the Downloads page. If no packaged installer exists yet, run the Electron app from the companion folder for development testing.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <strong>Create a pairing code</strong>
      <p class="muted">Open Client Monitor, click Create Pairing Code, then enter the short-lived code in GS Agent. Pairing this PC once keeps it connected until you revoke it or clear local app data.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <strong>Confirm heartbeat</strong>
      <p class="muted">The connected device should show a recent Last Seen value. Jobs will queue only for your own Discord user workspace.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <strong>Enable local monitoring if needed</strong>
      <p class="muted">Client detection and snapshots are opt-in settings. Snapshots should target selected windows and avoid secrets.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <strong>Run a controlled job</strong>
      <p class="muted">Start with a simple Browser Automator job or launch profile. Watch Local Jobs for queued, running, waiting-for-user, completed, or failed status.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="panel">
  <div class="panel-head">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Safety Requirements</p>
      <h2>Automation rules that cannot be removed</h2>
    </div>
    <span class="tag">Production boundary</span>
  </div>
  <div class="checklist-grid">
    <p class="row-line"><span>CAPTCHA, Cloudflare, 2FA, phone, and email verification</span><strong>Pause for user</strong></p>
    <p class="row-line"><span>Browser windows</span><strong>Visible</strong></p>
    <p class="row-line"><span>Automation start</span><strong>User-triggered</strong></p>
    <p class="row-line"><span>Saved login/email/password fill</span><strong>Allowed for the logged-in owner in visible jobs</strong></p>
    <p class="row-line"><span>Client monitoring</span><strong>Opt-in status detection only</strong></p>
    <p class="row-line"><span>Game client injection, memory reads, scripts, session/cookie theft</span><strong>Not supported</strong></p>
    <p class="row-line"><span>Logs</span><strong>No passwords, OTP secrets, tokens, cookies, or raw encrypted values</strong></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="panel">
  <div class="panel-head">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Quick Compatibility</p>
      <h2>What to configure first</h2>
    </div>
    <a class="button small" href="/compatibility">Full Matrix</a>
  </div>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Best first action</th><th>Status</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <% matrix.forEach(item => { %>
        <tr>
          <td><strong><%= item.name %></strong><br><span class="muted"><%= item.type %></span></td>
          <td><%= item.notes %></td>
          <td><span class="status <%= item.status %>"><%= item.status %></span></td>
        </tr>
      <% }) %>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
<%- include('partials/foot') %>
